shorewall-nft (1.11.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Release 1.11.0: libnftnl-integration phases 0-7 closed.
    New rule-file ACTION verdicts: SYNPROXY (TCP SYN-cookie engine),
    QUOTA (byte-budget cap), CONNLIMIT(N[:mask]) (concurrent-connection
    cap, action form). New mangle-file ACTIONs: TPROXY (transparent-
    proxy divert) and DUP (tap-copy). New parser surface: ?DYNSET
    directive (auto-blacklist on probe), HEADERS column (IPv6
    extension-header match), and the previously-ignored secmarks
    file is now compiled (WP-F2: SELinux MAC labelling via named
    secmark objects + per-rule meta secmark set). Dynamic blacklist
    chain now emits an IPv6 sibling rule + dynamic_blacklist_v6 set
    so blacklisted IPv6 sources are dropped (the v4-only emit
    pre-1.11.0 silently bypassed v6). Capability probe coverage
    closed for has_masquerade, has_redirect, has_tproxy_stmt,
    has_synproxy_stmt, has_synproxy_obj, has_flow_offload,
    has_dup, has_fwd, has_exthdr, has_dynset, has_connlimit,
    has_secmark_obj. --strict-features now catches every nft-native
    feature at compile time. simlab grew an NftOracle for nft-only
    feature classification (probe class I — SYNPROXY half-open
    SYN cookie intercept).

 -- André Valentin <avalentin@marcant.net>  Sat, 25 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

shorewall-nft (1.10.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Release 1.10.2: Phase 6 upstream-Shorewall config-coverage parity.
    Full snat / classic 1:1 nat / providers (multi-ISP) / routes / rtrules /
    tcinterfaces (HTB/HFSC/cake) / tcpri / synparams / blacklist / hosts
    OPTIONS / interfaces OPTIONS extras / zones IPsec OPTIONS /
    proxyarp+proxyndp nft emit / disposition settings / dynamic blacklist
    modes / LIMIT / CONNLIMIT / LOG_LEVEL+LOG_BACKEND+LOG_GROUP /
    MarkGeometry / IP-alias setup. New CLI: generate-iproute2-rules.
    pyroute2-first standard locked: zero new production shell-outs.
    Architecture: P8 backend-pluggable + P9 resource-efficient agent
    execution principles added.  Maintenance refactors:
    runtime/pyroute2_helpers extracted (8 _idx + 16 settings_bool sites
    consolidated); FirewallIR list fields fully typed; BackendEmitter
    protocol scaffolded for future VPP/eBPF backends.
    Tests grew 1041 -> 1616 (+575).
